Quality affordable child care is a growing problem as more women work
outside the home. Companies offer assistance such as subsidies,
referral services and on-site centers, finding it raises employee
morale and increases productivity.  Daycare wages remain the lowest of
any major occupation. Nannies earn $150 to $450 per week.
